'''Nala Hetsime''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] from [[Pa Tho]], who had joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] by [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]]. In that [[Standard year/Legends|year]], Hetsime was stationed at [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]. He participated in the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]] as part of the Rebel [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Group]] under the [[Callsign/Legends|call sign]] [[Rogue Seven/Legends|Rogue Seven]] against the invading [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Blizzard Force/Legends|forces]]. While the battle resulted in a Rebel defeat, Hetsime's [[Snowspeeder/Legends|snowspeeder]] made it through the battle intact.

==Biography==
[[File:RebelPilotHoth7.jpg|thumb|left|275px|Nala Hetsime listens to Princess Leia Organa's briefing prior to the Battle of Hoth.]]
Nala Hetsime was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] from [[Pa Tho]] who lived during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. He<ref name="EGW" /> served as a [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].<ref name="ESB" /> In the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] to [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]].</ref> he was stationed at [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]].<ref name="ESB" /> Hetsime was part of the base's pilot contingent consisting of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Flight]], [[Blue Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Blue Squadron]], and [[Green Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Green Squadron]]. During the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], when the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] discovered Echo Base, Rogue Group was formed from the three Rebel [[Squadron/Legends|squadrons]].<ref name="EGW" /> Hetsime was a part of that formation,<ref name="JKTCG" /> under the [[Callsign/Legends|call sign]] of [[Rogue Seven/Legends|Rogue Seven]], with [[Cinda Tarheel/Legends|Cinda Tarheel]] serving as his [[Gunner/Legends|gunner]].<ref name="EGW" />

[[File:Rogue_Group_TESB_Manga.jpg|250px|thumb|The twelve airspeeders of Rogue Group, including pilot Hetsime, attack during the Battle of Hoth.]]
Shortly after the Empire's invasion of Hoth, Hetsime joined the rest of Rogue Group to listen to a briefing held by [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], who discussed Echo Base's evacuation plans. The various Alliance [[Transport/Legends|transports]] would depart Hoth one by one, under the cover fire of the base's [[V-150 Planet Defender/Legends|v-150 Planet Defender]], and escorted by two [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]], which they hoped would allow the [[Starship/Legends|ships]] to slip by the Imperial [[Blockade/Legends|blockade]] in [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]] of the planet.<ref name="ESB" /> Hetsime took part in defending Echo Base from the invading Imperial [[Blizzard Force/Legends|Blizzard Force]].<ref name="JKTCG" /> Although the battle ended with the Rebels being forced to retreat from their base,<ref name="ESB" /> Hetsime and Tarheel's [[Snowspeeder/Legends|snowspeeder]] made it through without getting shot down.<ref name="EGW" />

==Personality and traits==
Dour and laconic, Hetsime was a mystery to his fellow pilots, who failed to draw more than the most basic information out of him. Nonetheless, they couldn't argue with his bravery in the [[Cockpit/Legends|cockpit]].<ref name="EGW" /> Nala Hetsime had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and fair skin.<ref name="ESB" />

==Skills and abilities==
A good pilot, Hetsime could fly anything&mdash;whether it was streaking through [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] or a few [[Meter/Legends|meters]] above Hoth.<ref name="JKTCG" />

==Equipment==
Hetsime wore the standard [[Rebel flight suit]] along with a [[Flight helmet/Legends|flight helmet]] and [[Goggles/Legends|goggles]] during his service as a Rebel pilot.<ref name="JKTCG" />

==Behind the scenes==
Nala Hetsime's T-47 first appeared in [[1999]]'s [[Star Wars Manga: The Empire Strikes Back 1|''Star Wars Manga: The Empire Strikes Back'' 1]], an adaption of [[1980]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']].<ref name="Empire Manga 1">[[Star Wars Manga: The Empire Strikes Back 1|''Star Wars Manga: The Empire Strikes Back'' 1]]</ref> He was first named on a card for [[2001]]'s [[Masters of the Force (Jedi Knights TCG)|''Masters of the Force'']] expansion set of [[Decipher]]'s ''[[Jedi Knights Trading Card Game]]'', though the character was not linked to any character in the ''Empire Strikes Back'' film.<ref name="JKTCG" /> Hetsime was [[Tuckerization|named as]] an anagram of the "[[Wikipedia:Alan Smithee|Alan Smithee]]" pseudonym used by [[Wikipedia:Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] directors.<ref name="Tweet">{{Twitter|CCGHistory|status/1398310018177540097|CCG History ([[Chuck Kallenbach]] as guest)|quote=on the latest episode of our #TheBoosterPack podcast*, guest @chuckkallenbach—designer of many Star Wars games—revealed this little-known secret about a certain character in the #StarWars universe [regarding the origins of Nala Hetsime's name]|archivefile=File:Nala_anagram.png}}</ref> In [[2013]], Nala Hetsime was established as one of the extra Rogue Squadron pilots seen in ''The Empire Strikes Back'' in the [[Rogues Gallery (department)|''Rogues Gallery'']] feature of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' [[Star Wars Insider 146|146]].<ref name="Insider">{{InsiderCite|146|Rogues Gallery|Rogues Gallery: Clearance for Immediate Launch}}</ref>

